## Enumerations

### enum  {#ab33e9e639814daad35bb1a9dc84190c0}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="enum llvm::FileCheckDiag::MatchType ">
What type of match result does this diagnostic describe?

<EnumerationList title="Enumeration values">

<Link id="ab33e9e639814daad35bb1a9dc84190c0adcf3e4ffa0433fb40711377d53b4baf1" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MatchFoundAndExpected">
Indicates a good match for an expected pattern
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ab33e9e639814daad35bb1a9dc84190c0a66b95270a54c88af1ba70b794aa836f8" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MatchFoundButExcluded">
Indicates a match for an excluded pattern
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ab33e9e639814daad35bb1a9dc84190c0a3f5c9c6115db2361e358de0c62d43bed" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MatchFoundButWrongLine">
Indicates a match for an expected pattern, but the match is on the wrong line
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ab33e9e639814daad35bb1a9dc84190c0abf168517cbdcc053154c47b20986837b" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MatchFoundButDiscarded">
Indicates a discarded match for an expected pattern
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ab33e9e639814daad35bb1a9dc84190c0ab7e91555667e7182c229428b8f3a6302" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MatchFoundErrorNote">
Indicates an error while processing a match after the match was found for an expected or excluded pattern
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ab33e9e639814daad35bb1a9dc84190c0a4a92716c994d8a58dc2e6b158e2b2f3f" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MatchNoneAndExcluded">
Indicates no match for an excluded pattern
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ab33e9e639814daad35bb1a9dc84190c0afc543db8ad6f068fab3eea06297e0ebc" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MatchNoneButExpected">
Indicates no match for an expected pattern, but this might follow good matches when multiple matches are expected for the pattern, or it might follow discarded matches for the pattern
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ab33e9e639814daad35bb1a9dc84190c0ad139fc8ba0eace914c3d91f8c51c35b1" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MatchNoneForInvalidPattern">
Indicates no match due to an expected or excluded pattern that has proven to be invalid at match time
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ab33e9e639814daad35bb1a9dc84190c0a6c8cff7a0ac871bde6a0e4e33a8e90d2" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MatchFuzzy">
Indicates a fuzzy match that serves as a suggestion for the next intended match for an expected pattern with too few or no good matches
</EnumerationListItem>

</EnumerationList>

A directive&#39;s supplied pattern is said to be either expected or excluded depending on whether the pattern must have or must not have a match in order for the directive to succeed. For example, a CHECK directive&#39;s pattern is expected, and a CHECK-NOT directive&#39;s pattern is excluded.

There might be more than one match result for a single pattern. For example, there might be several discarded matches (MatchFoundButDiscarded) before either a good match (MatchFoundAndExpected) or a failure to match (MatchNoneButExpected), and there might be a fuzzy match (MatchFuzzy) after the latter.
